      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that use error, as a factor, pertains primarily to physical device operation by clinical end-users and does not apply to a fully automated CFD pipeline executed within a controlled HPC environment. Accordingly, no formal use-error assessment was conducted. The factor is not-assessed rather than not-applicable because a structured argument was not formally documented in the credibility plan — an omission that is material given the elevated Model Risk Level 3 context, where unreviewed analyst decisions in simulation setup could propagate undetected bias into hemolysis predictions."
